  "texts": [
    "Testing such algorithms on real vehicles is often a costly (and sometimes even dangerous) task.",
    "In recent years, with the rapid Development of machine learning-based algorithms in the field of autonomous driving, there has been a need for large volumes of driving data for training and testing.",
    "Existing autonomous driving datasets have limitations in one or more important aspects, including scene variability, richness of annotations, and geographic distribution.In addition, models trained on existing datasets tend to overfit domain-specific features.",
    "This subsection will introduce some commonly used generic traffic scenario datasets and scenario-specific datasets for autonomous driving.",
    "This section will introduce some commonly used datasets for traffic scenarios, and most of them are summarized in Table 4, table 5, table 56, and Table 7."
  ]
}